Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our Veggie Cheeseburger Inspired Rice Bowl in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

> Serve with Baby Gem Salad for a complete meal.

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{0.25%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

Trim the @Baby Gem Lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a medium #bowl{}, combine the @Cider Vinegar{15%ml}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Olive Oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing (see pantry for both amounts). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the baby gem to the dressing. Toss to coat, then set aside.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @Unconventional Plant-Based Burgers{2} to the pan and use a #spoon{} to mash into a mince-like texture as it cooks.

Cook until the plant-based mince is browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Ensure they're piping hot throughout.

Add the garlic, @Tomato Puree{30%g} and @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} to the pork. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, @Honey{1%tbsp} and @Water{100%ml} for the plant-based mince (see pantry for both amounts). Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the baby gem salad and spiced plant-based mince.

Sprinkle over the cheese and drizzle over the @Burger Sauce{45%g}.

Enjoy!